Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: gXor
Version: 0.1
Summary: XOR(gamma-sequence) symmetric enc/dec method
Home-page: https://github.com/j7sx/gXor
Author: Sergey S. aka j7sx
Author-email: joker66s@mail.ru
License: BSD
Download-URL: https://github.com/j7sx/gXor/tarball/master
Description: XOR symmetric encryption method to secure the "imposition" of a sequence consisting of random numbers on the plaintext.
        The sequence of random numbers is called the gamma-sequence and is used to encrypt or decrypt data.
        
        Example:
        
        import gXor
        
        g = gXor.Gamma()
        
        enc = g.crypt("Hi, my name is ... !", "asd123")
        print (enc)
        >>> х7azтядcсск.цhж 019
        
        dec = g.decrypt(enc, "123asd")
        print (dec)
        >>> hi, my name is ...!
        
        enc = g.crypt("Привет, как тебя зовут?", "123апу4")
        print (enc)
        >>> ikdгх61ze4лg6a3z.ияцpl2
        
        dec = g.decrypt(enc, "123апу4")
        print (dec)
        >>> привет, как тебя зовут?
Keywords: xor,gamma,gamma-sequence
Platform: UNKNOWN
